 the Himalaya talk borders into existence, and also how those borders speak to them and their identities. These ‘talking borders’ exist in a world where state borders are contested, and which is being irrevocably transformed by rapid social and economic change. This book offers a new perspective on this dynamic region by centring language, and in doing so, also offers new ways of thinking about how borders and language influence each other.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBorderlandszHimalaya Mountains Region. 0aBoundariesxSocial aspects. 0aBoundaries. 0aSociolinguisticszHimalaya Mountains Region. 0aTibetan languagexSocial aspects. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aLanguage Studies. 4aSouth Asia. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aHimalaya, linguistic anthropology, borders, Tibet.1 aDonohue, Cathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyslop, Gwendolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyslop, Gwendolyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLepcha, Charisma K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoche, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoche, Gerald, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchendel, Willem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuzuki, Hiroyuki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Shannon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam 